node.text: Today, we honor those who have served. But moreover, those who didn't come home. Those who's lives are forever changed. Take a moment. Think of them. Think of how your life benefits, from their sacrifice. How are you going to honor them? Take the opportunities provided to you, that they can't. Be it by disability, or sacrifice, for your ability to live your life as you choose. Their lives were cut short for you, or forever changed. Make them proud. Make it all worth it. Own that dash between the two dates, because theirs ran short. Remember them.

Odysseus, on his journey home, is visited by a ghost. The ghost tells him that once he reaches his home  once he slays his enemies and sets his house in order  he must do one more thing before he can rest. The ghost says he must take up an oar and walk inland, and keep walking until someone mistakes that oar for a shovel. For that would be a place where no man has ever been troubled by the sea, and that's where he'd find peace.
